# Source / generated split (SPEC-map-tracker.md P1).
#
# COMMITTED SOURCE stays tracked: the stylized hull SVGs, the coordinate facts
# (map_calibration*, region_centroids*, region_pins* -- the committed pins let the pack build with no
# coord dump present), the hand-authored Lua glue (logic/autotracking/init), manifest, and layouts.
#
# GENERATED OUTPUT below is (re)built by tools/gen_poptracker.py from the greenfield apworld + the
# committed coord facts. It churns with every apworld edit, so it is not tracked -- run
# build_poptracker.ps1 (or `python tools/gen_poptracker.py`) before packaging.

# rasterized map images (from the committed SVGs; heavy binaries)
images/maps/*.png

# merged PopTracker map def (base + DLC map_defs)
maps/maps.json

# AP-id / region maps derived from the apworld data model
scripts/loc_map.lua
scripts/loc_dlc.lua
scripts/ap_map.lua
scripts/region_graph.lua

# location / item tables derived from the apworld data model
locations/locations.json
items/items.json
layouts/item_grid.json
